# CLAUDE.md — Global Instructions

## Skill management

When the user asks to manage, list, inspect, create, edit, delete, backup, restore, or validate Codex Skills, use the `skill-manager` helper script.

Skill manager path: `~/.agents/skills/skill-manager/scripts/skillctl.py`

### Available commands

```bash
SKILLCTL=~/.agents/skills/skill-manager/scripts/skillctl.py

# View
$SKILLCTL list                        # list all installed skills
$SKILLCTL search <keyword>            # search by keyword
$SKILLCTL read <skill-name>           # read skill metadata + first 80 lines
$SKILLCTL read <skill-name> --full    # read complete skill
$SKILLCTL locations                   # show managed directories

# Validate
$SKILLCTL validate --all              # validate all skills
$SKILLCTL validate <skill-name>       # validate one skill

# Manage
$SKILLCTL create <name> --description "..."   # create new skill
$SKILLCTL backup <skill-name>                  # backup skill
$SKILLCTL delete <skill-name>                  # dry-run delete (preview)
$SKILLCTL delete <skill-name> --yes            # safe delete (backup + trash)
$SKILLCTL restore <trash-or-backup-path>       # dry-run restore
$SKILLCTL restore <trash-or-backup-path> --yes # confirm restore

# Migration
$SKILLCTL export                                # export skills only → Desktop
$SKILLCTL export --include-all-user-config      # export everything (skills+AGENTS+hooks+prompts)
$SKILLCTL export --output <path>                # export to custom path
$SKILLCTL verify-archive <archive.tar.gz>       # verify archive integrity
$SKILLCTL import <archive.tar.gz>               # dry-run import (preview)
$SKILLCTL import <archive.tar.gz> --yes         # confirm import (merge mode)
$SKILLCTL import <archive.tar.gz> --yes --mode overwrite      # overwrite mode
$SKILLCTL import <archive.tar.gz> --yes --mode skip-existing  # skip existing

# Version
$SKILLCTL --version                   # skillctl.py 1.0.0
```

### Safety rules

- Never permanently delete a skill without backup.
- Delete operations: backup first, then move to `.trash/`. Require `--yes` for actual move.
- Import operations: always dry-run first, show conflicts, then ask before `--yes`.
- Never modify system-level or admin-level skills.
- Never modify business project code.
- Keep output concise. Do not paste full files unless asked.

### Repository

https://github.com/mygitall/skill-manager

To install: `git clone https://github.com/mygitall/skill-manager.git && cd skill-manager && bash install.sh`
